      • setSindex

        public void setSindex(java.lang.String sindex)
        Sets the sindex, Iindex, Lindex, and Indexed(true) as appropriate.
        Index will become 0 if a NumberFormatException would otherwise result.
        SAFSInvalidActionArgumentRuntimeException is thrown if a valid string index is provided whose value is less than 0.
        Parameters:
        sindex - The sindex to set
        Throws:
        SAFSInvalidActionArgumentRuntimeException( - getProperty() )
